      <li>Window=&gt;Show Configuration
        <ul>
          <li>Press Add Configuration.  Do NOT select the Active checkbox for New Configuration!</li>
          <li>Find your Audio Devices (Audio MIDI Setup) window. Locate the â€œInâ€ and the â€œOutâ€ column in this window.
            <ul>
              <li>Where you see a zero, you donâ€™t have a device.  Where you see a 2, you have two devices.</li>
              <li>The devices are numbered from the top, starting with zero.  The input devices are counted separately from the output devices.
                <ul>
                  <li>i.e. Youâ€™ll have input devices zero and one, and output devices zero and one, and if you have more than one input/output, youâ€™ll have higher numbers too.</li>
                </ul>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>In the Configuration window, set Input I and Input Q to the input devices you want to use.  If you set them both to zero and one, youâ€™ll use the first input device and the first output device listed in the Audio Devices window.</li>
          <li>Scroll a little to the right, and set input gain and output gain to 20</li>
          <li>Now you can set the Active checkbox for your new configuration.  As soon as you do, you should start hearing hissing, if your Softrock is connected.</li>
          <li>Close the Audio Devices window and the Configuration window.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
